children.subject: If you do well in 70 and like cs61B/70, I highly recommend 170. But 170 is the hardest out of the three. 188 and 100 are about the same difficulty and has some overlap.

history.content:
Hey everyone!

As the phase 1 approaches, I am thinking about the technical courses I am going to take next semester.

I am a sophomore. After this semester I will have taken CS 61A/B, 70, EECS 16A/B (currently taking cs 61b, eecs 16b).

A reasonable choice is CS 61C as not taking it next semester will limit my choice of upper-divisions for the next fall. I am currently thinking about the other technical; the following upper-divisions do not require 61c - CS 170, 188, Data 100. I would highly appreciate if you could recommend which one to take and why.

Thanks in advance
history.subject: Choosing CS classes for Spring 2022
